record_data.record_plain_text: 1. Availability. Seller may sell electric energy and capacity under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale. Seller may also sell ancillary services under this Rate Schedule into the ISO New England ("ISO-NE"), PJM Interconnection, LLC ("PJM"), New York Independent System Operator ("NYISO"), and other markets, and on a bilateral basis within those market areas. The ancillary services that Seller makes available under this Rate Schedule include: (a) New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the NYISO. (b) New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO-NE. (c) PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity, or ancillary services by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Seller or of the NYISO, ISO-NE, or PJM. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: The following limitations and exemptions or waivers to the Commission's regulations apply to sales under this Tariff: (a) Seller is exempt from Parts 41, 101 and 141 of the Commission's regulations, except for Parts 141.14 and 141.15. Dkt. No. ER02-2080-000, Letter Order (July 12, 2002). (b) Seller has blanket authorization for the issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to section 204 of the FPA, 16 U.S.C. 824(d). Dkt. No. ER02-2080-000, Letter Order (July 12, 2002). (c) Seller is exempt from the provisions of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, with the exception of sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16. Dkt. No. ER02-2080-000, Letter Order (July 12, 2002). 7. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a), in the Northeast Region, and a Category 1 seller in the Central, Southeast, Southwest, Southwest Power Pool, and Northwest Regions.

ESSENTIAL POWER OPP, LLC Rate Schedule FERC No. 2 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Essential Power OPP, LLC ("Essential Power OPP") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a natural gas-fired generating facility located in Lakewood, New Jersey ("Facility") in the control area administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule sets forth Essential Power OPP's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
